reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice, sturdy table for the price
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice sturdy little table for the price. It has good weight and doesn't wobble. I bought the brown/black combo and it is a really pretty wood grain. I really bought this for the USB and electric outlets on the top and it really keeps my phone and tablet cords more organized and out of the way. It took longer to put together than I liked, but that was not a big deal. I am really happy with this table and would recommend it. It's pretty, compact, and I love having the extra outlets!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I’ll be honest guys- I was skeptical about two end tables for this price- I’m very pleased with what I receivedThe “wood” laminate is nice- i realize the white spot in the photo looks like a scratch- it’s just styrofoam from the packing- this looks niceIt was easy to assemble - call up your friend with all the Tea and drama while you assemble and it will be done in no timeVery pleased- outlets work as labeled. Definitely smaller- if you’re looking for big end tables, look elsewhere- however if you’re looking for space efficient, sturdy and affordable, this is your spot 👌🏼

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars cute and affordable
reviews.reviewText: It doesn’t feel like the most sturdy piece of furniture i’ve used but as long as you don’t misuse and abuse it, it’s sturdy enough to get the job done for a good while and worth the price. It was pretty easy to follow along the instructions but it still took me about a full 45-60 minutes, it’s super cute and sleek but the only thing someone might be mad at is the screws showing in the four corners on top, doesn’t bug me too much.

reviews.reviewText: Perfect height for my bed and the plugs work great, only thing is that two iPhone charging blocks cannot be plugged in at the same time as the plugs are too close but it’s not too much of a problem. Still overall an awesome product!

reviews.reviewText: Small, but we wanted small! Perfect for beside tables :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I like it! Here are a few things…
reviews.reviewText: I followed a reviewer's suggestion and utilized my electric screwdriver with a 3mm hex bit, spending 45 minutes assembling it—a task I'm skilled at. When using the electric screwdriver, be cautious towards the end of screwing to avoid over-tightening and potentially cracking the wood. Pay attention to the sticker positions in the instructions; for instance, if the 'B' sticker is indicated on top, align the piece accordingly when attaching the legs. The side table looks fantastic, fits precisely where intended, and I appreciate the convenient plug and USB at the top. I highly recommend this side table!
